sentences: Gerry Hemingway (born March 23, 1955) is an American jazz drummer and composer.
Hemingway was a member of the Anthony Braxton quartet from 1983 to 1994.
Hemingway received a Guggenheim Fellowship for his work in music composition in 2000, and was a student of Alan Dawson.
